value.title: Biden says the US will not enter lockdown despite COVID delta variant threat
value.excerpt: President Biden on Friday said the United States will not enter another "lockdown," despite the "serious and deadly threat" of the delta variant of COVID-19, while touting the 300 million COVID-19 shots administered to Americans in less than 150 days.

value.title: Biden taps ex-Boies partner to lead DOJ policy office

value.title: Biden’s First Task at Housing Agency: Rebuilding Trump-Depleted Ranks

value.title: Donald Trump endorses Kelly Tshibaka for Senate in race against Lisa Murkowski
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump endorsed Alaska GOP Senate candidate Kelly Tshibaka on Friday, pledging to campaign against Republican Sen. Lisa Murkowski, who voted to convict him of inciting the deadly insurrection at the Capitol on January 6.
